  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And so the first opportunity was on the 3rd of October.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We went over to [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Hronia. ?] And that's where we saw a hopeless situation there, because we were automatically-- we knew automatically they were Jewish people because of the yellow [? sign. ?] And I said, well, to my wife, I don't know what's going on, but something is going to happen anyhow because the station was full.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And oh well, we stayed the whole day in [?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Hronia, ?] and came back late in the afternoon.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And then we saw it approaching the station in from Westerbork was [?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Hoholland. ?] And from there on, all the people arrived there and had to walk down about four and a half to 5 kilometers to the camp.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Well, ?] they were all packed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And well, these people couldn't carry all these things, so they left their baggage on the roadside.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And from the camp later on, that was collected.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But gee, that was a mess, a complete mess.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In one day, that's what I got to know afterwards, the camp commander got the message from the German authorities that they were going to bring in slack-- that was the word, slack-- so all at once, approximately 16,000 people.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it happened that [? today. ?] So that evening, we had approximately 20,000 people in the camp, for a capacity of, at that time, not more than 10.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So these people couldn't get their accommodation.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They couldn't be fed, because the kitchen couldn't cope with the situation at all.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was very bad.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the next day people were waiting even outside.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I remember that particular transport.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
